@Node "OVERVIEW" "EnvoyARexx.guide/OVERVIEW"
@Next "ARCHIVE"
@Prev "COPYRIGHT"
@Toc "Main"

Overview
********

   The purpose of @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub} is to transmit ARexx-commands (and thus
execute  whole ARexx-scripts) over an Envoy network.

   @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub} is able to create ARexx-ports on the local machine. Any
incoming  message will be converted to an Envoy-transaction and sent to
the appropriate  remote machine. The service running on the remote will
convert the transaction  to an ARexx-message and forward it to the
ARexx-port of the real application.   The result of the messages
(returned by the application) will be converted back to an
Envoy-transaction and replied to the local machine. The library on the
local  machine will convert the result for use within the ARexx-message
and replies the  message. See also @{"Archive overview" Link "ARCHIVE"}.

   Additionally, you can 'connect' to the @{i}COMMAND@{ui}-'port'(1) of a remote
machine. Thus, you can easily run commands on a remote machine in the
network.

   A diagram may elucidate thoughts:

                                       <- Function-calls
             -----       rexxsys.library  <---------->    ARexx-scripts
                |              |               Results ->       |
                |   Function-  |                                |
                |      calls   |  Results               Results | RexxMessages
                |              |                                |
                |              |               Results ->       |
     Local      |      envoyarexx.library <----------> emulated ARexx-port
                |              |       <- RexxMessages
                |              |
                |              |
                |              |  Transactions
                |              |
                |            Envoy
             -----             |
                               |
                            Network
                               |
             -----             |
                |            Envoy
                |              |
                |              |  Transactions
                |              |
                |              |          RexxMessages ->
     Remote     |      envoyarexx.service <----------> ARexx-port ('host')
                |                      <- Results               |
                |                                               |
             -----                                         Application

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1)  This port isn't  actually a port, but can be accessed just like
a port by ARexx-scripts.


@EndNode

@Node "ARCHIVE" "EnvoyARexx.guide/ARCHIVE"
@Next "INSTALL"
@Prev "OVERVIEW"
@Toc "Main"

Archive overview
****************

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}envoyarexx.library@{ub}: ARexx function-library. Interface between
     ARexx and Envoy. Adds functions to ARexx when added to your
     system. Creates local  ARexx-ports and forwards incoming
     ARexx-messages, receives the results from the  remoted machines
     and sends them back to their reply-port. In the network-language
     you would call this library a client.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}envoyarexx.service@{ub}: Envoy-alike service. Receives messages from
     a client, converts them to ARexx-messages an forwards them to the
     desired  destination port. Sends back the result to the
     appropriate client. This  Envoy-service is a server.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}ConnectHost@{ub}: Creates a communication-path from the local
     @{i}envoyarexx.library@{ui} to a remote @{i}envoyarexx.service@{ui}. Opens an
     ARexx-port on the local machine, ready to receive and forward
     ARexx-messages.   (1)

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}DisConnectHost@{ub}: Removes a commnuication-path which was
     previously  created by @{i}DisConnectHost@{ui} or by the appropriate
     ARexx-function of the  library. Causes the @{i}envoyarexx.library@{ui} to
     close the local ARexx-port.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Install_EnvoyARexx@{ub}: Automatic installation-script for
     @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}EnvoyARexx.(guide|dvi)@{ub}: This manual. :-)

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1)  Please note that the @{i}envoyarexx.library@{ui} provides compatible
functions for ARexx-scripts.


@EndNode

