@Node "INSTALL_MANUAL" "EnvoyARexx.guide/INSTALL_MANUAL"
@Prev "INSTALL_AUTO"
@Toc "INSTALL"

Manual installation
===================

   If you want to install @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub} by hand (for what reason ever) you
should  copy:

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}envoyarexx.library@{ub} in your LIBS: directory or wherever your
     scripts will find this file. The library is only needed on those
     machines  which should run ARexx-scripts and/or run the
     @{i}ConnectHost@{ui} command for example.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}envoyarexx.service@{ub} in your Envoy/Services directory. The
     service  is only needed on target-machines which actually run a
     ARexx-application. Please  make sure to enable the service with
     the @{i}Services Configuration@{ui} program.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}ConnectHost@{ub} and @{b}DisConnectHost@{ub} are the CLI-equivalents  of the
     @{i}envoyarexx.library@{ui}'s functions and thus only needed if you want
     to establish connections-paths 'by hand' or via batch-files. The
     @{i}ConnectHost@{ui}  and @{i}DisConnectHost@{ui} commands need the
     @{i}envoyarexx.library@{ui}.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}EnvoyARexx.guide@{ub} should - of course - be installed on every
     machine  in your network, to come handy when you need it and to
     disturb you when you don't. ;-)


@EndNode

