Rexx function description
*************************

   The following functions are implemented in the @{i}envoyarexx.library@{ui}
for usage  within ARexx-scripts. Please note that there are
compatible(1) CLI commands of these functions.   See also @{"CLI commands" Link "CLICOMMANDS"}.

   Please remember that you have to CALL ADDLIB('envoyarexx.library',
0, -30), before  you can use these functions within ARexx-scripts.


 @{" CONNECTHOST() " Link "REXX_CONNECTHOST"}                 
 @{" DISCONNECTHOST() " Link "REXX_DISCONNECTHOST"} 

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1)  compatible  means that it's possible to remove connections with
the CLI command  @{i}DisConnectHost@{ui}, which were originally established by
using the ARexx-function  CONNECTHOST() and vice versa.


@EndNode

@Node "REXX_CONNECTHOST" "EnvoyARexx.guide/REXX_CONNECTHOST"
@Next "REXX_DISCONNECTHOST"
@Toc "REXXFUNCTIONS"

CONNECTHOST()
=============

@{b}NAME@{ub}
     CONNECTHOST() - Establish an @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub}-connection to a remote
     ARexx-port

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
     CALL CONNECTHOST (Remote_Machine,Remote_ARexxPort,Local_ARexxPort)

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
     Creates a connection to a public port on a remote Amiga. Invokes
     the  @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub}-service on the remote machine. No connection will
     be made,  if the desired port can't be found on the remote
     machine. After  usage, the connection should be removed with the
     DISCONNECTHOST() function  or the @{i}DisConnectHost@{ui} CLI command.

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}
           CALL CONNECTHOST ("RIKER","Ed")
           CALL CONNECTHOST ("CORE","COMMAND","COMMAND.CORE")

@{b}INPUTS@{ub}
       1. Remote_Machine: Hostname of the remote Amiga.

       2. Remote_ARexxPort: Case-sensitive name of the public port you
          wish to  connect to on the remote machine. The remote port
          must be findable via  @{i}FindPort()@{ui} and should be an ARexx-port,
          of course.

       3. Local_ARexxPort: Name of the appropriate public port that
          should be  opened on the local Amiga. This argument is
          optional(1) and defaults to the name of @{i}Remote_ARexxPort@{ui}.
          This name is case-sensitive, too.


@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
     The ARexx-variable @{i}RC@{ui} contains a specific error-code.   See also
     @{"Errorcodes and -messages" Link "ERRORS"}.

   ---------- Footnotes ----------

   (1)  However, this  argument is required for @{i}COMMAND@{ui} remote ports.
You can never open a local  port named @{i}COMMAND@{ui}!


@EndNode

@Node "REXX_DISCONNECTHOST" "EnvoyARexx.guide/REXX_DISCONNECTHOST"
@Prev "REXX_CONNECTHOST"
@Toc "REXXFUNCTIONS"

DISCONNECTHOST()
================

@{b}NAME@{ub}
     DISCONNECTHOST() - Remove a connection to a remote ARexx-port

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
     CALL DISCONNECTHOST (Local_ARexxPort)

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
     Closes the connection to the remote port, removes the local port
     from Exec's  list and frees it. Ports, that were not created by
     the CONNECTHOST() function or  the @{i}DisConnectHost@{ui} CLI command,
     won't be touched.

@{b}EXAMPLE@{ub}
           CALL DISCONNECTHOST ("Ed")
           CALL DISCONNECTHOST ("COMMAND.CORE")

@{b}INPUTS@{ub}
       1. Local_ARexxPort: Case-sensitive name of the public port,
          whose connection  to the remote port should be removed.


@{b}RESULTS@{ub}
     The ARexx-variable @{i}RC@{ui} contains a specific error-code.   See also
     @{"Errorcodes and -messages" Link "ERRORS"}.


@EndNode

