CLI commands
************

   The following CLI commands are provided for manual use or for usage
within AmigaDOS-scripts (batch-files). Compatible ARexx-functions are
provided  for use within ARexx-scripts. See also @{"Rexx functions" Link "REXXFUNCTIONS"}.


 @{" ConnectHost " Link "CLI_CONNECTHOST"}                
 @{" DisConnectHost " Link "CLI_DISCONNECTHOST"} 


@EndNode

@Node "CLI_CONNECTHOST" "EnvoyARexx.guide/CLI_CONNECTHOST"
@Next "CLI_DISCONNECTHOST"
@Toc "CLICOMMANDS"

ConnectHost
===========

@{b}NAME@{ub}
     ConnectHost - Establish an @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub}-connection to a remote
     ARexx-port

@{b}TEMPLATE@{ub}
     HOST/A,REMOTEPORT/A,LOCALPORT,LIBRARY/K

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
     @{i}ConnectHost@{ui} acts just like the ARexx-function CONNECTHOST().   See
     also @{"CONNECTHOST()" Link "REXX_CONNECTHOST"}.

@{b}INPUTS@{ub}
       1. HOST: Hostname of the remote Amiga in your network.

       2. REMOTEPORT: Remote port to connect to.

       3. LOCALPORT: Local name for the remote port.

       4. LIBRARY: Path/filename of the @{i}envoyarexx.library@{ui}. This is
          optional  and useful if the library isn't located in LIBS:.




@EndNode

@Node "CLI_DISCONNECTHOST" "EnvoyARexx.guide/CLI_DISCONNECTHOST"
@Prev "CLI_CONNECTHOST"
@Toc "CLICOMMANDS"

DisConnectHost
==============

@{b}NAME@{ub}
     DisConnectHost - Remove a connection to a remote ARexx-port

@{b}TEMPLATE@{ub}
     LOCALPORT/A

@{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
     @{i}DisConnectHost@{ui} acts just like the ARexx-function DISCONNECTHOST().
     See also @{"DISCONNECTHOST()" Link "REXX_DISCONNECTHOST"}.

@{b}INPUTS@{ub}
       1. LOCALPORT: Name of the local port to remove.




@EndNode

@Node "EXAMPLE" "EnvoyARexx.guide/EXAMPLE"
@Next "ERRORS"
@Prev "CLICOMMANDS"
@Toc "Main"

First example
*************

   @{b}Example.earexx@{ub} is a very simple example-script for @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub}.
Please edit the remote machine's name in the script before you start
(rx Example.earexx) it.

   The script first attempts to connect to the @{i}COMMAND@{ui}-port of the
remote,  to run the @{i}Ed@{ui} editor. After this, the script will send the
quit command  over the network. As a result, @{i}Ed@{ui} will return a warning
(20), which is  returned over the network.

   The output looks like this:


      Connecting to RIKER port COMMAND
      Disconnecting
      Connecting to RIKER port Ed
       65 *-* ADDRESS 'LocalEd' 'q';
      +++ Command returned 20
      Disconnecting


@EndNode

@Node "ERRORS" "EnvoyARexx.guide/ERRORS"
@Next "BUGS"
@Prev "EXAMPLE"
@Toc "Main"

Errorcodes and errormessages
****************************

   @{b}*@{ub} 0 - @{i}no error@{ui}: everything ok.

   @{b}*@{ub} 1 - @{i}unknown error@{ui}: error occured, cause not known.

   @{b}*@{ub} 2 - @{i}destination port not found@{ui}: the destination port was not found
     on the remote Amiga. Check if the application is running on the
     remote machine.

   @{b}*@{ub} 3 - @{i}no response space@{ui}: size of the data to be replied exceeds the
     reply-buffer size.

   @{b}*@{ub} 4 - @{i}reply immediate@{ui}: this is not really an error and should never
     occur.

   @{b}*@{ub} 5 - @{i}warning@{ui}: generic warning.

   @{b}*@{ub} 10 - @{i}generic error@{ui}

   @{b}*@{ub} 20 - @{i}fatal error@{ui}

   @{b}*@{ub} 21 - @{i}no child-process@{ui}: the library was unable to create the
     child-process.

   @{b}*@{ub} 22 - @{i}no messageport@{ui}: unable to create messageport.

   @{b}*@{ub} 23 - @{i}no reply-messageport@{ui}: unable to create reply-messageport.

   @{b}*@{ub} 24 - @{i}no host or service@{ui}: service or host not found. May also
     indicate an Envoy-error.

   @{b}*@{ub} 25 - @{i}no file-handles@{ui}: unable to open file-handles for
     SystemTagList().

   @{b}*@{ub} 26 - @{i}local port already exists@{ui}

   @{b}*@{ub} 27 - @{i}port not found or alien@{ui}: this error occurs if you try to
     disconnect a non-existing or a foreign port.


@EndNode

@Node "BUGS" "EnvoyARexx.guide/BUGS"
@Next "SECURITY"
@Prev "ERRORS"
@Toc "Main"

Known bugs/problems
*******************

   The following problem encountered so far: An ARexx-command, which
doesn't return  a result 'immediately' (a command that waits for
user-input, for example) may cause  an timeout-error, when the
Envoy-timeout span is elapsed.

   The timeout for RexxMessage-transactions is currently set to 200
seconds, which  should be enough in most cases, but can be too much in
some cases, anyway. Future  versions of @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub} may provide a
function to control the timeout by  the ARexx-script dynamically.


@EndNode

@Node "SECURITY" "EnvoyARexx.guide/SECURITY"
@Next "AUTHOR"
@Prev "BUGS"
@Toc "Main"

A word about security
*********************

   Right now, @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub} is totally insecure. Everyone can connect from
everywhere to every port on a machine where the @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub}-service  is
installed. This belongs also to the delicate @{i}COMMAND@{ui}-port, of course.
Be warned!

   If anyone thinks that security is a must-have for @{b}EnvoyARexx@{ub}, please
contact me. ;-)


@EndNode

